"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-26-captain-fraser-pryce-aims-inspire-jamaicans-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Three-time Olympic gold medalist Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce says she is very honoured and privileged to be restored with the task of being the female captain of Jamaica's team at the Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 56, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\"}, {\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999763918131378, \"rank\": 1.8865321701237548e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9997714003166418, \"rank\": 0.00022865195304123004, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce, who is attending her fifth Olympics, is captaining the Jamaica team for the second time in her illustrious career, which has yielded eight medals at the Games.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 274, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999763918131378, \"rank\": 1.8865321701237548e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The iconic athlete toldThe Jamaica Observerin an exclusive interview on Friday that she hopes her legacy in the sport will help inspire the next generation of Jamaican athletes.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999872108137839, \"rank\": 1.2788476646809152e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is about representation and representing excellence, and that is what the legacy is for me,\\\" said Fraser-Pryce.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It represents excellence and really just leading the team and leading from the front, giving them hope.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope that I will be able to add inspiration to their journey, and whatever event they are doing, there is something they can take from the story and legacy as well.\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been an honour to represent; this is not the first time that I am captaining the team,\\\" Fraser-Pryce noted.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1063, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old, a 10-time world champion, highlighted that she is excited about the captaincy and will do her best to assist young athletes on the team in whatever way she can.\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This moment is special because I remember when I started on my first Olympic team in 2008, and being here is such a good feeling to see other young athletes coming in and the ones who are eventually going to take control of what is to come for Team Jamaica,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So to be captain of this team is really an honor and privilege,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": []}]}"